cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as instance segmentation, depth order estimation, and occlusion detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel convolutional neural network architecture, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep learning techniques to estimate the semantics-aware distance map also makes it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with robotics-related tasks such as object detection and segmentation, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper uses the COCOA and D2SA datasets, which are commonly used in multimedia-related tasks, making it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
